radiusNumAuthServers.name: radiusNumAuthServers
radiusNumAuthServers.description: The maximum number of RADIUS authentication servers supported by the system.

radiusNumAcctServers.name: radiusNumAcctServers
radiusNumAcctServers.description: The maximum number of RADIUS accounting servers supported by the system.

radiusAuthStatsTable.name: radiusAuthStatsTable
radiusAuthStatsTable.description: A list of entries for RADIUS authentication statistics.

radiusAuthStatsEntry.name: radiusAuthStatsEntry
radiusAuthStatsEntry.description: An entry containing object variables to describe a session.

radAuthServerIndex.name: radAuthServerIndex
radAuthServerIndex.description: The index number for this session status entry. Its value ranges from 1 to 'radiusNumAuthServers'. and identifies which server entry is associated with.

radAuthLoginRqstSent.name: radAuthLoginRqstSent
radAuthLoginRqstSent.description: Total number of authentication requests sent. These requests are strictly for authentication purposes. The sum of this value and 'radAuthOtherRqstSent' represents the total number of requests sent (excluding RADIUS accounting requests).

radAuthOtherRqstSent.name: radAuthOtherRqstSent
radAuthOtherRqstSent.description: Total number of requests sent that are NOT related to authentication or accounting. These include requests for routes, filters, banners, etc.

radAuthRqstTimedOut.name: radAuthRqstTimedOut
radAuthRqstTimedOut.description: Total number of authentication requests which timed out. Value should be less than or equal to 'radAuthLoginRqstSent'.

radAuthOtherRqstTimedOut.name: radAuthOtherRqstTimedOut
radAuthOtherRqstTimedOut.description: Total number of requests excluding authentication and accounting which timed out. Value should be less than or equal to 'radAuthOtherRqstSent'.

radAuthRspRcvd.name: radAuthRspRcvd
radAuthRspRcvd.description: Total number of responses to authentication requests received. Response could be a NAK or an ACK. Value should match radAuthLoginRqstSent. The sum of this value and 'radAuthOtherRspRcvd', 'radAuthUnexpRspRcvd', and 'radAuthBadRspRcvd' represents the total number of responses received (excluding those related to RADIUS accounting).

radAuthOtherRspRcvd.name: radAuthOtherRspRcvd
radAuthOtherRspRcvd.description: Total number of responses to requests that were NOT related to authentication or accounting. Response could be a NAK or an ACK. Value should be less than or equal to radAuthOtherRqstSent.

radAuthUnexpRspRcvd.name: radAuthUnexpRspRcvd
radAuthUnexpRspRcvd.description: Total number of responses received that did not match an outstanding request. A positive value may indicate configured timeout is insufficient. Total excludes accounting responses.

radAuthBadRspRcvd.name: radAuthBadRspRcvd
radAuthBadRspRcvd.description: Total number of authentication responses received that were rejected due to: (1) authentication NAKed. (2) invalid authenticator field. (3) invalid packet format. (4) invalid code field. (5) unrecognized attribute. A positive value may indicate mismatch in the shared secrets.

radAuthAckRspRcvd.name: radAuthAckRspRcvd
radAuthAckRspRcvd.description: Total number of authentication requests which were ACKed or authenticated successfully. Value is less than or equal to 'radAuthLoginRqstSent'.

radAuthHostIPAddress.name: radAuthHostIPAddress
radAuthHostIPAddress.description: The IP address of the Authentication server. The value 0.0.0.0 is returned if entry is invalid.

radAuthCurrentServerFlag.name: radAuthCurrentServerFlag
radAuthCurrentServerFlag.description: Value indicates whether this entry is the current authentication server or not. Writing a value will cause the current server to be reset.

radiusAcctStatsTable.name: radiusAcctStatsTable
radiusAcctStatsTable.description: A list of entries for RADIUS accounting statistics.

radiusAcctStatsEntry.name: radiusAcctStatsEntry
radiusAcctStatsEntry.description: An entry containing object variables to describe a session.

radAcctServerIndex.name: radAcctServerIndex
radAcctServerIndex.description: The index number for this session status entry. Its value ranges from 1 to 'radiusNumAcctServers'. and identifies which server entry is associated with.

radAcctRqstSent.name: radAcctRqstSent
radAcctRqstSent.description: Total number of accounting requests sent.

radAcctRqstTimedOut.name: radAcctRqstTimedOut
radAcctRqstTimedOut.description: Total number of accounting requests which timed out.

radAcctRspRcvd.name: radAcctRspRcvd
radAcctRspRcvd.description: Total number of responses to accounting requests received.

radAcctUnexpRspRcvd.name: radAcctUnexpRspRcvd
radAcctUnexpRspRcvd.description: Total number of accounting responses received that did not match an outstanding request. A positive value may indicate configured timeout is insufficient.

radAcctHostIPAddress.name: radAcctHostIPAddress
radAcctHostIPAddress.description: The IP address of the Accounting server. The value 0.0.0.0 is returned if entry is invalid.

radAcctCurrentServerFlag.name: radAcctCurrentServerFlag
radAcctCurrentServerFlag.description: Value indicates whether this entry is the current active accounting server or not. Writing a value will cause the current server to be reset.

radiusNewNASPortIDFormat.name: radiusNewNASPortIDFormat
radiusNewNASPortIDFormat.description: TRUE if new NAS port ID format is used, FALSE if old NAS Port ID is used. On the TNT product family the new NAS port ID format is used by default. The old format cannot be used for multi-shelf systems or if any line cards are in a slot greater than the twelfth position.
